Second Department,

August, 1942.

(August 3, 1942.) In the Matter of the Application of Harry M. Swirnoff, Petitioner, Respondent, for an Order Pursuant to Article XIV and Sections 330 and 335 of the Election Law, against S. Howard Cohen and Others, Commissioners of Elections of the City of New York, Constituting the Board of Elections of the City of New York, Respondents, and Donald J. Regan and Others, Appellants.

On the call of the calendar, on consent of the parties, the appeal is withdrawn. Lazansky, P. J., Hagarty, Johnston, Taylor and Close, JJ., concur.
